<inglise> COUNCIL DIRECTIVE 1999/13/EC of 11 March 1999 on the limitation of emissions of volatile organic compounds due to the use of organic solvents in certain activities and installations </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 1999/13/E&Uuml; teatavates toimingutes ja seadeldistes orgaaniliste lahustite kasutamise tulemusena tekkivate lenduvate orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite heitkoguste piiramise kohta 11. m&auml;rts 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 130s(1) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 130s l&otilde;iget 1, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 189c of the Treaty (3), </inglise>
<eesti> tehes otsuse asutamislepingu artikliga 189c etten&auml;htud korras (3) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas the European Community action programme on the environment approved by the Council and the representatives of the Governments of the Member States meeting within the Council by resolutions of 22 November 1973 (4), 17 May 1977 (5), 7 February 1983 (6), 19 October 1987 (7) and 1 February 1993 (8) stresses the importance of the prevention and reduction of air pollution; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) Euroopa &Uuml;henduse keskkonnaalases tegevusprogrammis, mis on heaks kiidetud 22. novembril 1973, (4) 17. mail 1977, (5) 7. veebruaril 1983, (6) 19. oktoobril 1987 (7) ja 1. veebruaril 1993 (8) n&otilde;ukogu ja n&otilde;ukogus kokkutulnud liikmesriikide valitsuste esindajate poolt vastuv&otilde;etud resolutsioonidega, r&otilde;hutatakse &otilde;husaaste &auml;rahoidmise ja v&auml;hendamise t&auml;htsust; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas in particular the resolution of 19 October 1987 emphasises the importance of Community action to concentrate, inter alia, on implementation of appropriate standards in order to ensure a high level of public health and environmental protection; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) eelk&otilde;ige 19. oktoobri 1987. aasta resolutsioonis r&otilde;hutatakse, et rahva tervise ja keskkonnakaitse k&otilde;rge taseme tagamiseks tuleks &uuml;henduse meetmetes keskenduda muu hulgas asjakohaste standardite rakendamisele; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas the European Community and its Member States are parties to the Protocol to the 1979 Convention on Long-Range Transboundary Air Pollution concerning the control of emissions of volatile organic compounds in order to reduce their transboundary fluxes and the fluxes of the resulting secondary photochemical oxidant products so as to protect human health and the environment from adverse effects; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) Euroopa &Uuml;hendus ja liikmesriigid on liitunud 1979. aasta piiri&uuml;lese &otilde;husaaste kauglevi konventsiooni protokolliga, mis k&auml;sitleb lenduvate orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite heitkoguste kontrolli, eesm&auml;rgiga v&auml;hendada nende piiri&uuml;lest levikut ja nendega kaasnevate sekundaarsete fotokeemiliste oks&uuml;dantide levikut ning kaitsta inimeste tervist ja keskkonda kahjuliku m&otilde;ju eest; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas pollution due to volatile organic compounds in one Member State often influences the air and water of other Member States; whereas, in accordance with Article 130r of the Treaty, action at Community level is necessary; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) lenduvatest orgaanilistest &uuml;henditest tingitud saaste &uuml;hes liikmesriigis m&otilde;jutab sageli teiste liikmesriikide &otilde;hku ja vett; vastavalt asutamislepingu artiklile 130r on vaja v&otilde;tta meetmeid &uuml;henduse tasandil; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas, because of their characteristics, the use of organic solvents in certain activities and installations gives rise to emissions of organic compounds into the air which can be harmful for public health and/or contributes to the local and transboundary formation of photochemical oxidants in the boundary layer of the troposphere which cause damage to natural resources of vital environmental and economic importance and, under certain exposure conditions, has harmful effects on human health; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) arvestades orgaaniliste lahustite omadusi, kaasnevad nende kasutamisega teatavate toimingute puhul ja seadeldistes orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite heitmed &otilde;hku, mis v&otilde;ivad olla kahjulikud rahva tervisele ja/v&otilde;i p&otilde;hjustada fotokeemiliste oks&uuml;dantide kohalikku ja piiri&uuml;lest teket troposf&auml;&auml;ri piirikihis, mis omakorda v&otilde;ivad kahjustada keskkonna ja majanduse seisukohalt olulisi loodusressursse ning teatavatel kokkupuutetingimustel inimeste tervist; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas the high incidence of high tropospheric ozone concentrations in recent years has triggered widespread concern regarding the impact on public health and the environment; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) troposf&auml;&auml;ri sagedase k&otilde;rge osoonikontsentratsiooni t&otilde;ttu viimastel aastatel on hakatud ulatuslikult muretsema selle m&otilde;ju p&auml;rast rahva tervisele ja keskkonnale; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas, therefore, preventive action is required to protect public health and the environment against the consequences of particularly harmful emissions from the use of organic solvents and to guarantee citizens the right to a clean and healthy environment; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) seet&otilde;ttu on vaja ennetusmeetmeid, et kaitsta rahva tervist ja keskkonda orgaaniliste lahustite kasutamisega kaasnevatest eriti kahjulikest heitmetest tingitud tagaj&auml;rgede eest ning tagada kodanikele &otilde;igus puhtale ja tervislikule keskkonnale; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas emissions of organic compounds can be avoided or reduced in many activities and installations because potentially less harmful substitutes are available or will become available within the coming years; whereas, where appropriate substitutes are not available, other technical measures should be taken to reduce emissions into the environment as much as economically and technically feasible; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite heitkoguseid on mitmetes toimingutes ja seadeldistes v&otilde;imalik v&auml;ltida v&otilde;i v&auml;hendada, sest t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt v&auml;hem kahjulikud asendajad on k&auml;ttesaadavad v&otilde;i muutuvad k&auml;ttesaadavaks l&auml;hiaastatel; kui vajalikud asendajad puuduvad, tuleks v&otilde;tta muid tehnilisi meetmeid, et v&auml;hendada heitmeid keskkonda niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd see on majanduslikult ja tehniliselt otstarbekas; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas the use of organic solvents and the emissions of organic compounds which have the most serious effects on public health should be reduced as much as technically feasible; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) rahva tervist k&otilde;ige enam kahjustavate orgaaniliste lahustite kasutamist ja orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite heitkoguseid tuleks v&auml;hendada niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd see on tehniliselt otstarbekas; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Whereas installations and processes which fall under this Directive should at least be registered if they are not subject to authorisation under Community or national legislation; </inglise>
<eesti> 10) k&auml;esolevas direktiivis k&auml;sitletud seadeldised ja protsessid peaksid olema v&auml;hemalt registreeritud, kui &uuml;henduse v&otilde;i siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktidega ei n&otilde;uta nende kasutusluba; </eesti>
<inglise> (11) Whereas existing installations and activities should, where appropriate, be adapted so that within an appropriate period they meet the requirements established for new installations and activities; whereas that period should be consistent with the timetable for compliance of Council Directive 96/61/EC of 24 September 1996 concerning integrated pollution prevention and control (9); </inglise>
<eesti> 11) vajaduse korral tuleks olemasolevaid seadeldisi ja toiminguid kohandada nii, et need asjakohase ajavahemiku m&ouml;&ouml;dudes vastaksid uutele seadeldistele ja toimingutele kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele; k&otilde;nealune ajavahemik peaks olema koosk&otilde;las n&otilde;ukogu 24. septembri 1996. aasta direktiivi 96/61/E&Uuml; (saaste kompleksse v&auml;ltimise ja kontrolli kohta) (9) j&auml;rgimise ajakavaga; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) Whereas the relevant parts of existing installations which undergo substantial change must, as a matter of principle, meet the new installation standards for the substantially changed equipment; </inglise>
<eesti> 12) olemasolevate seadeldiste oluliselt muudetavad osad peavad p&otilde;him&otilde;tteliselt vastama oluliselt muudetud seadmete suhtes kohaldatavatele uue seadeldise standarditele; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) Whereas organic solvents are used by many different types of installations and activities so that, in addition to general requirements, specific requirements should be defined and, at the same time, thresholds for the size of the installations or activities which have to comply with this Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> 13) orgaanilisi lahusteid kasutatakse paljude eri liiki seadeldiste ja toimingute puhul, mist&otilde;ttu lisaks p&otilde;hin&otilde;uetele tuleks kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata erin&otilde;uded, samuti nende seadeldiste suuruse ja toimingute ulatuse piirm&auml;&auml;rad, mis peavad vastama k&auml;esolevale direktiivile; </eesti>
<inglise> (14) Whereas a high level of environmental protection requires the setting and achievement of emission limits for organic compounds and appropriate operating conditions, in accordance with the principle of best available techniques, for certain installations and activities using organic solvents within the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> 14) seoses keskkonnakaitse k&otilde;rge tasemega tuleb teatavate orgaanilisi lahusteid kasutavate &uuml;henduse seadeldiste ja toimingute puhul m&auml;&auml;rata parimate olemasolevate meetodite p&otilde;him&otilde;tte kohaselt kindlaks orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite heitkogused ja asjakohased ekspluatatsioonitingimused ning neid j&auml;rgida; </eesti>
<inglise> (15) Whereas in some cases Member States may exempt operators from complying with the emission limit values because other measures, such as the use of low-solvent or solvent-free products or techniques, provide alternative means of achieving equivalent emission reductions; </inglise>
<eesti> 15) m&otilde;nedel juhtudel v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid vabastada ettev&otilde;tjad heitkoguste piirv&auml;&auml;rtuste j&auml;rgimisest, kui muude meetmetega, n&auml;iteks v&auml;hese lahustisisaldusega v&otilde;i lahustivabade toodete v&otilde;i meetodite kasutamisega, on v&otilde;imalik heitkoguseid samav&auml;&auml;rselt v&auml;hendada; </eesti>
<inglise> (16) Whereas emission-limiting measures adopted before the entry into force of this Directive should be taken into account in an appropriate way; </inglise>
<eesti> 16) asjakohasel viisil tuleks arvesse v&otilde;tta heitkoguste piiramise meetmeid, mis on v&otilde;etud enne k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&otilde;ustumist; </eesti>
<inglise> (17) Whereas alternative approaches to reduction may allow the objectives of this Directive to be achieved more effectively than by implementing uniform emission limit values; whereas, therefore, Member States may exempt existing installations from compliance with the emission limits if they implement a national plan, which will, within the timetable for implementation of this Directive, lead to an at least equal reduction in emissions of organic compounds from these activities and installations; </inglise>
<eesti> 17) heitkoguste v&auml;hendamise alternatiivv&otilde;imalustega on v&otilde;imalik saavutada k&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rke t&otilde;husamalt kui &uuml;htsete lubatud heitkoguste rakendamisega; seep&auml;rast v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid vabastada olemasolevad seadeldised libatud heitkoguste j&auml;rgimise n&otilde;udest, kui neis rakendatakse riiklikku kava, mille tulemusena k&otilde;nealuste toimingute ja seadeldiste t&ouml;&ouml;ga kaasnevad orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite heitkogused v&auml;henevad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendamise ajakava jooksul v&auml;hemalt niisama palju; </eesti>
<inglise> (18) Whereas existing installations falling under Directive 96/61/EC which are covered by a national plan can under no circumstances be exempted from the provisions of that Directive, including Article 9(4) thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> 18) direktiivis 96/61/E&Uuml; k&auml;sitletud ja riikliku kavaga h&otilde;lmatud olemasolevaid seadeldisi ei v&otilde;i mingil juhul vabastada k&otilde;nealuse direktiivi s&auml;tete, kaasa arvatud selle artikli 9 l&otilde;ike 4 j&auml;rgimisest; </eesti>
<inglise> (19) Whereas in many cases small and medium-sized, new and existing installations may be allowed to comply with somewhat less stringent requirements to maintain their competitiveness; </inglise>
<eesti> 19) paljudel juhtudel v&otilde;idakse uutel ja olemasolevatel v&auml;ikestel ja keskmise suurusega seadeldistel lubada j&auml;rgida pisut leebemaid n&otilde;udeid, et s&auml;ilitada nende konkurentsiv&otilde;ime; </eesti>
<inglise> (20) Whereas for dry cleaning a zero threshold is appropriate, subject to specified exemptions; </inglise>
<eesti> 20) keemilises puhastuses on asjakohane kohaldada nullm&auml;&auml;ra, kui kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud eranditest ei tulene teisiti; </eesti>
<inglise> (21) Whereas monitoring of emissions is required, including the application of measurement techniques, to assess the mass concentrations or the quantity of the pollutants whose release into the environment is permitted; </inglise>
<eesti> 21) hindamaks selliste saasteainete massikontsentratsiooni v&otilde;i kogust, mille juhtimine keskkonda on lubatud, on vajalik heitmeseire, kaasa arvatud m&otilde;&otilde;tmismeetodite kohaldamine; </eesti>
<inglise> (22) Whereas operators should reduce emissions of organic solvents, including fugitive emissions, and of organic compounds; whereas a solvent management plan is an important tool to verify this; whereas, although guidance may be given, the solvent management plan is not developed to the stage where a Community methodology can be established; </inglise>
<eesti> 22) ettev&otilde;tjad peaksid v&auml;hendama orgaaniliste lahustite heitkoguseid, sh lenduvaid heitkoguseid, samuti orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite heitkoguseid; selle kontrollimisel on oluliseks vahendiks lahustikasutuskava; olenemata jagatavatest juhistest ei ole lahustikasutuskava niisugusel m&auml;&auml;ral v&auml;lja t&ouml;&ouml;tatud, et saaks kehtestada &uuml;henduse metodoloogia; </eesti>
<inglise> (23) Whereas Member States have to establish a procedure to be followed and measures to be taken where emission limitations are exceeded; </inglise>
<eesti> 23) liikmesriigid peavad n&auml;gema ette heitmepiirangute &uuml;letamisel kohaldatava menetluse ja v&otilde;etavad meetmed; </eesti>
<inglise> (24) Whereas the Commission and the Member States should collaborate in order to ensure that information on the implementation of this Directive and on the progress of substitution options is exchanged, </inglise>
<eesti> 24) komisjon ja liikmesriigid peavad tegema koost&ouml;&ouml;d, et tagada k&auml;esoleva direktiivi elluviimist ja asendusainete v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamist k&auml;sitleva teabe vahetus, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Purpose and scope </inglise>
<eesti> Eesm&auml;rk ja reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise> The purpose of this Directive is to prevent or reduce the direct and indirect effects of emissions of volatile organic compounds into the environment, mainly into air, and the potential risks to human health, by providing measures and procedures to be implemented for the activities defined in Annex I, in so far as they are operated above the solvent consumption thresholds listed in Annex IIA. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on v&auml;ltida v&otilde;i v&auml;hendada lenduvate orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite keskkonda, peamiselt &otilde;hku juhtimisega kaasnevat otsest v&otilde;i kaudset m&otilde;ju ning t&otilde;en&auml;olist ohtu inimeste tervisele, n&auml;hes ette meetmed ja menetluse, mida rakendatakse I lisas m&auml;&auml;ratletud toimingute suhtes, kui nende lahustikulu on suurem IIA lisas loetletud piirm&auml;&auml;radest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Definitions </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. installation shall mean a stationary technical unit where one or more activities falling within the scope defined in Article 1 are carried out, and any other directly associated activities which have a technical connection with the activities carried out on that site and which could have an effect on emissions; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) seadeldis - paikne tehniline &uuml;ksus, kus teostatakse &uuml;ht v&otilde;i mitut artiklis 1 m&auml;&auml;ratletud toimingut ja muid k&otilde;nealuses kohas teostatavate toimingutega tehniliselt otseselt seotud toiminguid, mis v&otilde;ivad m&otilde;jutada heitkoguseid; </eesti>
<inglise> 2. existing installation shall mean an installation in operation or, in accordance with legislation existing before the date on which this Directive is brought into effect, an installation which is authorised or registered or, in the view of the competent authority, the subject of a full request for authorisation, provided that the installation is put into operation no later than one year after the date on which this Directive is brought into effect; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) olemasolev seadeldis - t&ouml;&ouml;tav seadeldis, enne k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&otilde;ustumist kehtivate &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt kasutusloa saanud v&otilde;i registreeritud seadeldis v&otilde;i seadeldis, mille kohta p&auml;deva asutuse arvates tuleb esitada t&auml;ieliku kasutusloa taotlus, tingimusel et seadeldis k&auml;ivitatakse hiljemalt &uuml;he aasta m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&otilde;ustumisest; </eesti>
<inglise> 3. small installation shall mean an installation which falls within the lower threshold band of items 1, 3, 4, 5, 8, 10, 13, 16 or 17 of Annex IIA or for the other activities of Annex IIA which have a solvent consumption of less than 10 tonnes/year; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) v&auml;ike seadeldis - IIA lisa kirjetes 1, 3, 4, 5, 8, 10, 13 v&otilde;i 17 nimetatud madalama piirm&auml;&auml;ra alla kuuluv seadeldis v&otilde;i IIA lisa muude toimingute jaoks etten&auml;htud seadeldis, mille aastane lahustikulu on v&auml;hem kui 10 tonni; </eesti>
<inglise> 4. substantial change </inglise>
<eesti> 4) oluline muutus - </eesti>
<inglise> - for an installation falling within the scope of Directive 96/61/EC, shall have the definition specified in that Directive, </inglise>
<eesti> - direktiivi 96/61/E&Uuml; reguleerimisalasse kuuluva seadeldise puhul k&auml;esolevas direktiivis esitatud m&auml;&auml;ratlus, </eesti>
<inglise> - for a small installation, shall mean a change of the nominal capacity leading to an increase of emissions of volatile organic compounds of more than 25 %. </inglise>
<eesti> - v&auml;ikese seadeldise puhul nominaalmahu muutus, mille tagaj&auml;rjel suureneb lenduvate orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite heide &uuml;le 25%. </eesti>
<inglise> Any change that may have, in the opinion of the competent authority, significant negative effects on human health or the environment is also a substantial change, </inglise>
<eesti> Oluline muutus on ka selline muutus, mis p&auml;deva asutuse arvates v&otilde;ib m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt kahjustada inimeste tervist, </eesti>
<inglise> - for all other installations, shall mean a change of the nominal capacity leading to an increase of emissions of volatile organic compounds of more than 10 %. </inglise>
<eesti> - k&otilde;ikide muude seadeldiste puhul nominaalmahu muutus, mille tagaj&auml;rjel suureneb lenduvate orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite heide &uuml;le 10%. </eesti>
<inglise> Any change that may have, in the opinion of the competent authority, significant negative effects on human health or the environment is also a substantial change; </inglise>
<eesti> Oluline muutus on ka selline muutus, mis p&auml;deva asutuse arvates v&otilde;ib m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt kahjustada inimeste tervist; </eesti>
<inglise> 5. competent authority shall mean the authority or authorities or bodies responsible under the legal provisions of the Member States for carrying out the obligations arising from this Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) p&auml;dev asutus - riigiorgan v&otilde;i asutus, kes liikmesriikide &otilde;igusnormide kohaselt vastutab k&auml;esolevast direktiivist tulenevate kohustuste t&auml;itmise eest; </eesti>
<inglise> 6. operator shall mean any natural or legal person who operates or controls the installation or, where this is provided for in national legislation, to whom decisive economic power over the technical functioning of the installation has been delegated; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) ettev&otilde;tja - f&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tab seadeldisega, kontrollib selle t&ouml;&ouml;d v&otilde;i kellele on siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt antud m&auml;&auml;rav otsustus&otilde;igus seadeldise tehnilise toimimise suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> 7. authorisation shall mean a written decision by which the competent authority grants permission to operate all or part of an installation; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) kasutusluba - kirjalik otsus, millega p&auml;dev asutus annab loa kogu seadeldise v&otilde;i selle osa kasutamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> 8. registration shall mean a procedure, specified in a legal act, involving at least notification to the competent authority by the operator of the intention to operate an installation or activity falling within the scope of this Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) registreerimine - &otilde;igusaktiga m&auml;&auml;ratletud menetlus, mille k&auml;igus ettev&otilde;tja v&auml;hemalt teatab p&auml;devale asutusele oma soovist kasutada k&auml;esoleva direktiivi reguleerimisalasse kuuluvat seadeldist v&otilde;i toimingut; </eesti>
<inglise> 9. emission shall mean any discharge of volatile organic compounds from an installation into the environment; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) heide - lenduvate orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite juhtimine seadeldisest keskkonda; </eesti>
<inglise> 10. fugitive emissions shall mean any emissions not in waste gases of volatile organic compounds into air, soil and water as well as, unless otherwise stated in Annex IIA, solvents contained in any products. </inglise>
<eesti> 10) lenduvad heitkogused - k&otilde;igi v&auml;ljuvates gaasides mittesisalduvate lenduvate orgaaniliste &uuml;hendite ja, kui IIA lisas ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti, siis ka mis tahes toodetes sisalduvate lahustite juhtimine &otilde;hku, maapinda ja vette. </eesti>
<inglise> They include uncaptured emissions released to the outside environment via windows, doors, vents and similar openings; </inglise>
